    chronologyEn: [
      'The world shaped by Pangu grows lush with plants and animals, yet remains silent without any thinking beings.',
      'Nüwa, a goddess with a human face and a serpent\'s tail, wanders alone and grows deeply lonely.',
      'Seeing her own reflection on the surface of a pool, Nüwa conceives the idea of creating beings like herself.',
